{
  "texts": [
    "The development of automated metrics that can simulate human judgment, such as BLEU for translation or ROUGE for summarization, facilitates more scalable evaluation processes [69,70].",
    "Research has emphasized the importance of domainspecific evaluation, where models are assessed based on their performance in tasks relevant to their intended application areas [40,71].",
    "The assessment of models' ethical and societal impacts, including bias detection and mitigation, is increasingly recognized as integral to comprehensive evaluation frameworks [71].",
    "The exploration of interactive evaluation setups, where models are tested in dynamic environments that mimic realworld usage, offers insights into their practical utility [13,72].",
    "Lastly, the integration of feedback mechanisms for continuous model improvement based on evaluation outcomes highlights the iterative nature of optimizing language model performance [13,73]."
  ]
}